review:
Spielberg won't make a movie that's less than 150 minutes, so this near perfect war film is devalued (like many Spielberg films) by overly-sentimental scenes scored with cheesy overly-dramatic orchestral music - scenes that are unnecessary for the advancement of the film. So, enjoy the scenes of battle - they are the best in film. Take a bathroom break when you start to see guys just sitting around and you hear music from an old Army commercial.<br/><br/>RealReview Posting Scoring Criteria:
